            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="1127" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1127">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 E W /2–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-19T19:00:00-04:00">February 19, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>80. Reurtel 131, February 19, 10 a.m.<note n="24" xml:id="d1127fn24">Not
                        printed.</note> For Uruguay to be invited to the San Francisco Conference it
                    should act by March 1. This is in accordance with a decision taken at
                        Yalta.<note n="25" xml:id="d1127fn25">See Protocol of the Proceedings of the
                        Crimea Conference, <ref target="frus1945Malta#pg_975">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, The Conferences at Malta and
                            Yalta, 1945, pp. 975</ref>, <ref target="frus1945Malta#pg_976">976</ref>.</note> Please inform President confidentially.</p>
                <p>After the declaration of war and before a representative of Uruguay signs the
                    United Nations Declaration, we should have a communication stating that Uruguay
                    has entered into a state of war, that it desires to adhere to the United Nations
                    Declaration, and that it has empowered a representative to sign on behalf of
                    Uruguay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
